  So Namira and I wanted to do something a little out of the ordinary for one of our upcoming Dagger nights.  We came p with 2 different ideas.<br>
<br>
1.) Doing tangler pygmies w/ AE wizzies and Trebuchets. Tangler pygmies bring around 8-12 pygmies when pulled. They drop pretty easily. The idea is to have a couple Wizzies do AE while 2-3 trebuchets pound the area with mortars. Obviously this would be VERY dangerous, but could be a lot of fun. I was thinking 2-3 AE wizards (and I think we only have Tarl, we may need to borrow Forich / Cewen), a pally or two running heal chant, maybe Hidien doing AE mez, healers of course, and ideally a BT theurgist (Darris).  So maybe this would be an alliance mini-event <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If we want to keep it smaller we can always do #2.<br>
<br>
2.) Ballista hunting Bonesnappers. This could be 2 groups, w/ each group running a ballista. Heavy healing would be needed. have the groups engage a Bonesnapper (which are those nasty giant Lyon crabs) and have 2-3 ballistas hammer them with bolts.  From what i've read, the bonesnappers are pretty nasty, but can drop some good stuff.<br>
<br>
We'd need to make a run to a supply keep before hand, and find a good pulling spot, because the siege equipment aint moving. This would give everyone a chance to use a Treb/ballista, while also netting some nice xps. Anyone have any input on this idea? Anyone know the AE size of a Treb hit?Has anyone ever even fought a Bonesnapper? Please comment <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
